reviews: Wonderful, helpful staff. Very pricey breakfast (35 euro/person). Plenty of options outside. Rooms and floors have discordant numbers (e.g., 20th floor may have rooms beginning with 24xx). Elevators to the rooms operate only with room key, but once you understand this it's simple unless you want to go to a different floor to see a friend since the elevator will not take you there. Otherwise, I like the elevators which are efficient, frequent and plentiful you just have to locate the one going to your floor. The rooms are very nice with a minibar and ice to be found outside in separate space. Concierge services are on the first floor (registration is on the second floor which you can access by elevator, escalator or stairs). But the staff at both places are friendly and eager to help you (and them to learn). To go to the rooftop in the hotel requires that you to pay 50 euros per person that is guarding the elevator to the roof unless you go up after 11 pm. I object to this charge by the hotel for guests staying there, and the view is not worth it in my opinion. The hotel is across from the Montparnasse Gare and there are many good restaurants in the vicinity including at least three major grocery stores along with some interesting sites and streets to walk through. A metro is very close by.

Stayed here for 7 nights for our holiday in Paris. Service was great from check in to concierge to helping us open wines we bought outside. The concierge helped me to book the taxi to CDG, smooth and reliable.
Our family room was spacious, and offered a great view to the Latin Quarter. Comfortable beds and well designed bathroom is exactly what we needed after long days in museums.
The location was very convenient. Only 3 mins walk to Montparnasse station, and there is super market 1 minute away, which opens as early as 7am.

Fantastic from beginning to end. Fernando was amazing at check in, the breakfasts were to die for and the rooms spectacular and the location was perfect to use the train to see all of the sights. Wouldn’t hesitate in recommending.

Excellent buffet breakfast with great variety. Best location to go up to the Montparnasse tower or the restaurant up on top to have the best lighted view of the Eiffel Tower at night. Very comfortable room. Very friendly staffs!

We stayed here as a part of a tour group. It was a modern hotel close to very good metro and train connections. The breakfast was absolutely over the top good, a made to order omelet station fresh juices. On weekends it opens at 7 and weekdays 6;30. It is walkable to many cafes and two "mall type" shopping areas.

Good & convenient location, friendly staff, and delicious breakfast.
Facilities are gorgeous and very comfortable.
Thank you Pullman Paris Montparnasse!
It was hard to leave.
I would highly recommend to anyone looking for their stay in Paris.
I can't wait to return! I will come back for sure.
Many thanks again!!!

We were booked into this hotel as the finale of a Viking Zürich to Paris trip. First, the high tech elevators wouldn't accept our "key" cards. According to the front desk, their electronic check-in system was on the fritz (the hotel is Once that was fixed and we were sitting in our room, someone else came in because it was their room, too (double-booked). After the front desk rebooked us, we found that at least two of the USB ports in our next room were broken, and that one of the standard European outlets was dangerously loose. The room phones are tablet computers, but the sound wasn't good. - we could hear the front desk but they couldn't hear us. Also no instructions to help us use them. The hotel reportedly has a lovely rooftop bar, but it cost 50 euros to be allowed to go up there. There are lots of high tech gee-whiz touches to the hotel, but maintenance seemed poor. We were told that the hotel had been refurbished about a year ago - it really shouldn't have had all of those problems. All hat and no cattle, as they say in TX - looks flashy but some of the innards are trashy.

Our tour group spent two nights here. Our room had a nice view of the city, a great a\c, coffee maker and tea kettle, robe and slippers, small fridge, safe, and bathroom amenities. The bed was perfect for us…very firm. Breakfast buffet was delicious and varied and appreciated the 6:30 opening time.

Our last interaction with the hotel staff was unfortunately not good. Our guide had ordered breakfast boxes for 4 of us leaving at 5 am. We gathered in the lobby at 4:45 and were told we couldn’t get our to-go breakfasts until exactly at 5am. Well of course we were already in our airport transfer vehicle at 4:55. So no breakfast for us. The front desk staff were not helpful at all.

The bed and pillows was very comfortable. The hotel and staff was very nice. The view from my room was spectacular. The staff at the Cafe in the lobby was also very nice. I would definitely recommend the Pullman Montparnasse.

My wife and I loved our stay, the room was clean, good smell, the breakfast was delicious and it was close to the Metro. I would say its not within walking distance to the center of Paris, but got used to the metro so it was easy to navigate. We don't speak french, but we manage to navigate around. Hotel staff were very helpful in advising.

We were staying at the Pullman Paris Montparnasse as part of our Cities of Lights river cruise, two night in Paris w/ an additional two nights extension. I have very mixed reviews of this hotel. The room was the best, comfortable mattress, separate water closet, very clean and modern, not to my taste but very new. Housekeeping did a great job in cleaning the room every day. Both reception and the concierge were as helpful as possible. The location is not the greatest in my view. According to the Viking website we should have been staying at the Pullman Paris Tour Eiffel but Viking changed hotels, citing that the Pullman Paris Tour Eiffel could not provide sufficient accommodations for all of Viking's hotel guests. And to that, Viking has Paris as part of a number of their river cruises or passengers can choose to have an pre or post stay like us, therefore in an area of the main lobby, Viking had an office area for local staff to answer questions for their guests. My major complaint is that the hotel is very large, accommodating almost 1,000 guests yet the restaurant that serves breakfast to hotel guests, Umami Burger Paris, has seating for only 280 guests. Most guests will have their breakfast included and given the numbers from Viking cruises plus other tour groups, breakfast was packed and chaotic. Especially all weekend - Sat, Sun and Monday, May 8, being a French holiday, most guests were up early to either leave for a tour, or the ship, or going home. The restaurant choose to open at 7 AM on Monday since it was a holiday, people were lined up and wrapped around the lobby to get into breakfast. That day, the hostess didn't bother getting our name or room number, just what tour were we with, and we didn't even have anyone take us to a seat, it was basically look for any available table. The line for hot breakfast lines was just one, with just one person making omelets. It was expected for you to get your own coffee at a specialty machine, there are only four of them, so getting coffee had long lines and took time. This made for a very unpleasant way to start the day and it was not relaxing at all. Aside from the fact that hot breakfast was not particularly good. If you didn't have breakfast included, it was 32 euros per person; not a good value. And this is the beginning of the tourist season. The restaurant needs to make several changes in order to accommodate the numbers - they know how many people have breakfast included - they have the lists at the hostess station. Either they open up much earlier to spread out the numbers or change how they serve customers breakfast. There is not enough wait staff, creamer should be already on every table, pots of coffee should be close by the tables and servers ready to pour for customers being seated. This was not the way for us to end our holiday. If you book at this hotel, don't get the breakfast included, go down the street to Ernest and have a civilized breakfast.

From the moment we arrived the warm greeting that we received was just the start of an amazing stay … the rooms are so spacious and clean - staff at breakfast are so friendly and there’s so much choice. Would 100% stay here next time we come to Paris

Absolutely terrible experience. Was not feeling well and needed ti place a simple room service order. Unlike most hotels where staff can bring card machine to room to charge for in-room dining, Pullman Montparnasse had no such ability norcould I type card number into very fancy tablet upon which I was placing room-service order and agent would not take card over phone despite explaining that entire reason for room-service order was because I was not feeling well. Customer service agent insisted that I must come down from 24th floor to front desk and place card on room. When I arrived, it took front desk person 10+min to finally assist me, understand request and figure out how to attach credit card to room…he kept trying to issue me new room keys. By the time I returned to room 20+min later, the only restaurant that provides in-room dining had closed as with everything else in hotel so I was unable to order any type of food remedy to help ease ailment. Will NEVER stay at this hotel again. Customer service is snobbish, stuffy, difficult and unfriendly. It doesn’t deserve a single star.

Stayed at the Pullman Montparnasse for our Paris leg of our Euro Trip. The bed was the best of the 4 countries we visited with nice pillows. The staff were very helpful, courteous and polite all the way. Our luggage had a small crack at the bottom and I liked that we could communicate via Whatsapp and the hotel willingly gave us some tape so we could fix it up! The room has a small tablet that provides recommendations etc. Hotel is also close to the Gaite metro station although area is slightly quieter compared to the Les Halles area we stayed previously but of course at a more expensive price. Still felt relatively safe. The gym is awesome with lots of equipment! There is also a Skybar at the top!

Great hotel in a great location! Across the street from the train station, we had access to all of the sites in Paris easily. The room was nice and the bathroom was large. They use large bottles of toiletries which is a plus being environmentally conscious but housekeeping should ensure they are full. The gym is really nice and the check in and checkout process is quick. There are many restaurants around the hotel so there is no shortage of dinner options. For a family of 4 this is an ideal hotel. I’d stay here again when we visit Paris!

Clean rooms and comfortable accommodations and kind staff. The hotel breakfast was amazingly delicious and the workout room top notch. Location was great with the train across the street and access to so many landmarks.

Loved everything about the Pullman! Staff was incredible, location was fabulous, room was modern, clean and spacious. Lots of possibilities for food right out the front door. Two grocery stores are literally steps away. Restaurants and bakeries are a short walk towards the theater district. Metro and train access are directly across the street. Highly recommend this property!

Excellent weekend!
The room was very nice decorated as per my instruction ( we had bespoke service for my daughter 20th birthday, roses, Prosecco, cake and balloons ). The room was clean and the housekeeping should be appraised for it. Unfortunately we couldn’t go to see sky-bar we had no time. Breakfast excellent , unfortunately for lunch umami burger was disgusting so the chips with the cheese sauce. But all in all I would recommend the hotel to friends and family.

This hotel has been a wonderful spot for our family. Fernando at check-in made our experience the best ever. He was so kind to my kids and so helpful explaining everything the hotel has to offer. He made us feel so welcome for a long day of traveling.

I have only one negative comment regarding our two-night stay at this hotel: the bathroom. No counter space or storage for toiletries. Otherwise, the bed was very comfortable and the service was excellent. A positive is the close proximity to the train station/shopping mall.

i was a bit unsure about this hotel when i booked because there wasn't a lot of reviews, but when we arrived we were pleasantly surprised.

Staff:
When we arrived the lady at the desk was very helpful and went out of her way to she us around. There was also a lovely young lady at the burger restaurant she was kind and friendly.

Our Room:
The room was clean and a good size, the style is very nice with lots of mirrors which i loved, the bed was extremely comfy and the bed was changed in the morning which was unexpected as we were only staying for two nights. the view from our room was also very nice looking over the city we also got to see the sun setting.

Burger restaurant and Breakfast:
The food at the burger joint was ok but the burger was cold. breakfast was what you would expect from this type of hotel, pastries, eggs and sausages, pancakes and cereal tea coffee etc what let it down was that the food that should have been hot was cold even the hot water in the pot for tea was cold.

Location:
close to train station and shops/ restaurants.

all in all i rate this hotel 4/5 would have been a 5 but the food was cold.

Me and my family loved everything at this hotel. The room were comfy and the staff was very friendly, not to mention the breakfast was amazing everyday with options for everyone. Its location is great too, pretty close to so many attractions and you can walk to a lot great local places too! We will be back!

Great hotel, excellent staff and wonderful services.
The Front office team who are handling Accor members are very professional and really providing great hospitality.

Special thanks to Mr. Jerome the GM of the hotel for leading such wonderful team and exceeding guests expectations.

Mohamed Talaat, room 2230

Hotel is neat. Rooms are small. There is no door for the shower area. For Couples its fine. For two brothers or Sisters without a door for shower , how far it will be convenient Which i am not sure. Only one water bottle is kept every day. Additional Drinking water is chargeable - 13 Euro. Anything apart from the standard bath accessory, delivery charges 5 Euro is applicable. From both sides of the hotel you will not get Eiffel Tower View from the room. Only City View from all the rooms. Eiffel Tower View will be there from Skybar. Skybar entry is not free for the guests. Minimum Spend 50 Euros required per person to enter the Skybar. Train station is very close by. Many restaurants and shopping options are available in Montparnasse, which is very much close by to the Hotel. Montparnasse Tower is very close to the hotel , 5-7 minutes walkable distance. You can have a fantastic view of Paris from Montparnasse Tower.

Travelled with 2 adults and 2 kids (6 & 9). Room was clean, spacious and well appointed. But for the price and the brand that was expected. However the staff are not well trained, show no initiative or warmth. This is with the exception of Johan at the check in desk who was fabulous.

We arrived at the hotel on a cold windy Paris night with 2 young kids and 4 medium pieces of luggage. The concierge and doorman were more concerned with keeping themselves out of the cold wind then stepping out and helping us with the bags.

Dinner at their umami restaurant was underwhelming. Concierge gave us the wrong information with regards to a PSG game - incorrect directions and told us we wouldn’t need ID. Thank god we decided to follow the advice of Google instead and brought ID or we would not have been able to enter the stadium and watch the game we paid over 800+ euros for.

Icing on the cake was at checkout. It was raining heavily and the staff member at concierge instead of calling us a cab suggested we walk across the road with our 4 pieces of luggage and kids in tow!

No sense of hospitality from any of the staff (with the exception of Johan). If you are a family with young kids book with another hotel.

Good location, comfortable room, good food but staff - zero professionalism. I expected a lot from the brand and felt dissappointed by the way I had been treated, lack of communication between departments/indivudual staff members to transfer necessary information to avoid the situation the guests have to "fight" for services confirmed when booking the hotel.

We stayed at the Pullman Paris Montparnasse for one night and it was so incredible that I wish we could’ve stayed longer. When we arrived in front of the hotel from our Uber, the hotel staff literally ran outside to help us with our bags and walk us in. The staff were so attentive, friendly, and welcoming. Our room was so big with a beautiful view. Everything was very clean and felt very luxurious. The location of the hotel is perfect as it is right by a shopping center and train station.

We also went to the Skybar and it was stunning. Wonderful service, wonderful view, and amazing drinks. We also met some awesome people here. I would love to stay at this hotel again and have already recommended it to my friends.

Two successive stays in November, the first in two connected rooms #2030 + 2032 which went smoothly, and the second in Suite Deluxe #2042 with a very bad arrival experience. Check-in time is 3 pm. We arrived at the hotel at 2 pm, after having requested an early check-in (All Diamond privilege). We ended up getting our room at 4h45 pm which ruined our afternoon. Meanwhile, we were sent to the Platinum / Diamond lounge and then to a transit room, always with wrong misleading information on the timeline. Check-out time is noon. Hard to understand how the hotel can take 4h45 to prepare a room for its supposedly best customers. We complained and got some compensation, not alleviating the feeling that service is unreliable. The Suite Deluxe is made of two interconnected rooms, one of them being designed as a living room rather than as a bedroom. From our experience having tested the two options, it is better to take two interconnected rooms. At least the hotel has plenty of these, and you won't end up waiting for hours one of the few suites is ready when you arrive. Otherwise, most of the staff members seemed top-notch. But the hotel is so big it is hard for them to follow customers and provide tailored service by sharing information. All our accommodations were very clean and offered the expected views over Paris (27th floor). Some maintenance issues in one room were solved within 24h, which is acceptable. Good breakfast, but most of the restaurant's chairs are already stained (see picture). Too bad for a recently fully revamped property. Overall not sure we'll return.

We stayed at Pullman Montparnasse Paris for 3 nights and it was an amazing stay! The hotel is modern, remodeled, and super comfortable. Breakfast had so many different options. The staff was so nice, especially the concierge team and the grab and go on the 2nd floor. Valerie from the grab and go provided us with recommendations on cafes nearby! The metro was a 2 minute walk making it easy to get to most attractions like the Eiffel Tower, Louvre, etc. I must also say that housekeeping is superb. They did a great job keeping the room clean and refilling toiletries as there were 4 of us. My only recommendation would be to have a mini bar for guests (besides water). It goes a long way after traveling. Thank you Pullman Montparnasse, we can’t wait to be back! 😍

Now , call me old fashioned but I like a bathroom with a door on it . My very first impression of our room was - why is the shower in full view as soon as you walk into the room. There was a groove in the ceiling in the empty doorway so we genuinely looked for a slide door and couldn’t fathom it out . Anyway - we requested a curtain (which was fitted into the existing groove which was for hooks) for privacy . Strange set up though . However ! A pleasant stay apart from that - we did indeed have a lovely city view (Notre Dame ) . The bed and pillows were extremely comfortable (this was a deluxe room with a Queen bed) . We used the Whats App facility to request items (aforementioned curtain , and there was never enough cream/milk pots for drinks ) . Staff responded quickly and were always helpful and pleasant . Our room had not been ready when we arrived (at 8.30 in the evening ) - staff got us a drink at the bar and we waited for only 10 mins or so (still late though for a room not to be ready ) .
Getting around was easy as there is a Metro across the road and we purchased a card which took us through to Versailles and many metro trips (much easier than tickets ) . Go to the customers services at the station to do this they were so helpful .
We had one breakfast at the hotel - which was plentiful- loads of choice - but it was expensive . You can grab a much cheaper breakfast at any of the many many bistro/ brasseries which are everywhere.
A good stay - the hotel is very modern and if you like your tech and charging points it’s perfect. I didn’t even use the adapter plugs as they had a UK socket in the room as well which was great .

Location is a bit out of the way but good public transport is right across the street (Montparnasse train station). Restaurants, bakeries, supermarket and shops are all close by. The bed was comfortable with a good mattress and pillows and the room was an adequate size. Bathrobe and slippers are provided. The main thing I didn’t like about it was the bathroom which has only 3 walls. One of these is a swinging smoked glass door which did not close all the way. The lack of a wall made it difficult to warm the bathroom up. The shower, with its 2/3 glass partition, cannot help but get water on the floor but this is a common shower style in Europe. The lavatory was in its own room. Breakfast is very complete with many hot and cold offerings. There is a bar off the lobby which serves a basic pizza with a nice crust, and also a cafe with fresh take-away sandwiches if you don’t want to go out for dinner for some reason.

Sincerely I have been a bit disappointed by our accommodation. The room was a bit smaller than expected and the view (on the cemetery of Montparnasse) not very “charming”.
Anyhow we have got a quiet stay with a good breakfast buffet in the morning and a clean room, but if you compare the quality of this Pullman hotel with other ones in the world (I have been in Pullman Dubai for example) it’s a quite different story.
Anyhow, that’s Paris!
I also noticed a small lack of experience in the personnel, but I appreciate when young people are willing to work and to try their best. However, a mix of young and experienced people would be advisable.

Great Hotel next to the Montparnasse station - highly professional and international staff, trendy rooms with sophisticated bathroom, and smart elevators. Breakfast was excellent in the morning with a large variety of food for all types of guests. Not a romantic hotel, but more for business-orientated stays - ask for a room with a view!

This hotel is convenient to the Paris Metro, thus to any of the many attractions in Paris. All on the staff provided superb service. They have an excellent morning breakfast buffet. Our room was exquisitely comfortable and clean. For Americans who don't speak French, the front desk staff and many other staff members speak fluent English.

The hotel is newly renovated and looks very nice and it is very large which kind of makes is a bit soul-less.

They are trying very hard to give good service but it ends up being a hassle. I was greeted by a person when I walked in and he started to input my details in his iPad. I thought that I was being checked in but that was the concierge and I spent about 5 minutes with him. I then took the escalator to level 2 where the actual check in happened. I was given so much information that my check in took well over 10 minutes even though there was no que.

Room was ok but they have crammed too much furniture in there which made it difficult to move around the bed.

Wanted to have a drink in the bar after dinner but found that the lights were too bright and it didn't have any ambiance so we decided to go elsewhere.

I did not have breakfast included and tried to add that at check-in but that wasn't allowed. I was told to add to the room in the morning and then settle at check-out. At breakfast I first had to wait in line and then when trying to add my room to get charged for breakfast, they staff had to find yet another person so I ended up leaving without breakfast.

In my opinion the service doesn't run smoothly and even a simple task, like having breakfast charged to my room was difficult.

Location is great, I will come to the area again, but not to this hotel.

First class customer service! Very warm, welcoming, assisted with Ubers, Taxis, and directions.

Great location, close to everything, and main train station.

Only two drawbacks - there was a small on a couple of floors from a sewerage issue - but luckily never came into the room. Lastly, they charged a $50 min per person just to go upstairs and use the sky lounge. I feel as guests, that should be complimentary.

Over- I’d recommend

I came here for a conference with a lot of colleagues and stayed for a few days. On the plus side, the bed was comfy and the shower was good (two key requirements), the staff were polite and efficient, and as I was on the 22nd floor I had a great view to the north.

Sadly, however, there were other aspects that weren’t so great, including a sewage smell that was strong when I turned up but got progressively better over the few days that I stayed, the decor in the room that was a bit grey, the fact that the lift broke (did I mention I was on the 22nd floor), and the general location near the Montparnasse train station (I accept this is hardwired into the hotel, but it wasn’t my choice).

Ultimately, it was fine for a work trip, but I would have felt a bit cheated if I was here for a romantic trip to Paris…

We had a fantastic 5 nights stay with our 2 kids at Pullman Montparnasse. We arrived around noon and our room wasn’t ready yet so we had to wait a bit. We were offered drinks and snacks while waiting for check-in, and we were upgraded to a two-bed interconnecting family room on the 20th floor with great views of Paris. We absolutely loved our room.

The rooms were of great sizes and sparkly clean with sustainable bath amenities. However, there was no bathtub which was disappointing for a family room. There was also no iron in the room, but we requested for one and it was provided promptly.

The service was consistently great at all levels, and the staff went the extra mile to make our stay wonderful (eg. anticipating our needs and always chatting/playing with our kids). The hotel seemed busy during our stay but we didn’t feel this at all.

Breakfast buffet had a huge selection of food except they didn’t provide French toast and avocado which was a bit weird. And they always ran of pancakes!

Cons:
Our stay was prepaid but our card was debited for no reason on our last day (in addition to the €550 holding fee that was taken on our first day). Staff explained that this was a mistake and will be sorted out same day. However, it took several emails and nearly two weeks later for our money to be refunded and we weren’t pleased at all.

Overall, we loved our stay and would return when next we’re in Paris.

I used to stay at this hotel in the past, prior to the long renovation work, that they started a couple of years ago, and that they only recently finished.
I always had good experiences in the past, so I decided to go back, for the first time since they reopened, to see how it looked like now.
When I arrived I went upstairs, as this is where you check in now. After queuing for 10 minutes, I reach the reception desk, the receptionist, instead of checking me in, tells me to go to the Diamond check-in, as if queing a second time was the privilege they were offering me as an All Diamond member. It was not a good start.
When I get into the room, I notice the TV is stuck loading the system menu, I restart it many time same problem. I give up.
At 22h30, we decide to order food. I try to use the tablet, it is not intuitive, and I am an IT and technology guy, so I know what I am talking about, it takes too much time to load the pages, and you lose your order basket in the middle of the ordering process. I give up as well, I order by phone.
One hour later, at 23h30, our food hasn’t arrived yet.
I cannot reach the room service, instead I have a receptionist playing the intermediary between me and the room service. The later, obviously doesn’t help the communication, nor does it help locating my order.
The receptionist tells me he is calling me back in a few minutes, he never called back.
23h45, I call back, asking the same question, where is our food? Same answer, he is calling us back. He never calls back.
Midnight, wearing my bathrobe and sleepers, I go downstairs to the recption to complain, I tell them that, as a Diamond member, I was expecting a better service than waiting 1h30 minutes for my food order, the lady at the reception totally ignores me and instead, move away, and goes to take care of another guest.
Finally someone, takes care of my complaint, and call the room service, they tell him that my order is just arriving now at my room.
I go back up to my room, the food is there, however, it is only one part of what we have ordered, they forgot the fruit salad.
But this is not yet the worse, my friend taste the chocoloate mousse and she goes immediately to the barhroom to throw up, they have put vinegar in the chocolate mousse! She asks me to taste it, I just smell it, it stinks vinegar, I cannot even touch it.
They will finally not charge us for the food, but this didn’t help much, the experience was bad from A to Z, they are cleary totally disorganized since reopening, their IT is not working, the service is very poor.
It was the first time I went there after their renovation, and it will be the last.

Attended a big conference at Paris Expo this weekend. The Pullman staff was extremely helpful before I arrived, could WhatsApp them re my requests well ahead arrival. Maryanne at checkin reception was extra nice and helpful. Breakfast is great. I had a room with a nice view on 28th floor. Clean and modern. Concierge very helpful and courteous. Taxi drivers and locals all v nice to me (Asian tourist) in Paris. Incredible transformation compared with 20 years ago. Must come back. Convenient to the Metro and train station

This was a clean, modern hotel with courteous staff. I am especially grateful to the technician Florian Selva whose knowledge and service I was impressed by. I had issues with wifi connection, which was very important for my work. Even though I needed his help very late at night and was frustrated, he was so patient, calm, and guided me through the problem (and the problem was actually with my laptop). Thank you Florian, and thank you to all the staff for your kind and patient service.

A Rom-Com script does not play out better than this. In fact, if I saw it in a movie, I might question its feasibility.
My girlfriend and I stayed there for six days.
The rooms were clean and the beds were great. The shower designs tried to hard in every room (I will explain how we go to several in a moment), and simply garnered water all over the floor.

While the hotel was lovely, we had multiple problems:
On night three, we were awakened in the middle of the night by someone smoking in either a room nearby or in the hallway.
I called down at 3:30 AM to complain and was told security would be sent. The smell did not dissipate for hours and we were up until 5:30 AM, having to get up at 6:30 a.m. for our itinerary. Not a good night at all.
Upon our return from our plans, we went to the front desk and asked what had happened and if the person was spoken with. They said they had not spoken with the smoker and initially suggested we just "see what happens and call if there is a problem."
Not a good solution, as we would possibly be awoken again by the smoke, and I mentioned this.
They kindly moved us to another room on the 31st floor, citing an upgrade.
Upon arrival in our new room, we laid down as we were tired and immediately started hearing noise over our heads.
We called the front desk and asked what was over us. They said they would get back to us. My partner said, "Can you please find out? We don't want to be making this same call at 9:00 PM tonight.
At 9:30 PM, we still had not received the call but did hear very loud dance music from above us. We called down to complain and it turns out, we were moved to right below their nightclub, the Skybar, and the very thing we had hoped would not happen (a late night call) was happening, as no one remedied the problem.
We were moved again. This time to the 27th floor.
The room was fine, but on our last day, as we were trying to rest before leaving, we were blasted by a loud fire alarm. Afraid for our lives, we dashed down the stairs in states of undress and eventually made it down to the lobby.
When we got there, we were met by staff who comedically had a piece of paper that we never received stating that they were to be holding fire drills on our floor. We had not been informed and thought the hotel was on fire!
The hospitality manager, Florencia, tried to take care of us, getting us some breakfast and wiping the last breakfast off of our bill.
She went to look into refunding us several days but told us that as we bought the bundle through BJs (a nightmare in and of itself), we would have to look to get this taken care of through BJs.
We never got comped for the room, just a breakfast.

If offered, I would stay there again as the accommodations were nice, but what a frenetic fiasco.
Maybe, some fodder for a script, if nothing else.

the hotel was great, rooms are big enough,every thing is so clean in bed rooms and you have all things that you need except iron ,but shampoo,body lotion,slippers ,espresso and tea maker is available and they charge them every morning,breakfast was so wonderful and varied. our room was completely quiet and the bed was so comfortable,all in all we had unforgettable experience in this hotel ,and I recommend that to others

Our family of 4 was quite impressed by this hotel. Rooms are quite spacious and the check in process was seamless. There are toiletries provided in the bathroom, which is a nice touch. The location of this hotel is a bit out but there is a train station nearby, which helps. Supermarket literally next door, which is great.
The only thing that was a bit of a letdown was breakfast. The selection is great, a big range to choose from, but I found most of the 'hot' food cold (eggs, bacon, pancakes ... all cold). For the price we were paying for this, I found this disappointing and surprising. Not sure why this is the case? Bit of a letdown, but otherwise, quite a good hotel.
A filtered water tap, especially during summer, would not go astray in the lobby, to allow travellers the chance to fill up before heading out.

Good hotel, good location, good service and friendly staff. nice gym- but could benefit from a swimming pool and sundeck.
Outstanding concierge services from Juan and Luigi- thanks so much! Overall excellent, but (i) the 11.00am fire alarm is such a stupid time to conduct such an invasive exercise and (ii) it is cheaper to buy new clothes than use the hotel laundry service. Luckily there was a launderette 500 metres away.

Family and I had a great visit to Paris staying at the Pullman Montparnasse. From check in to check out, staff were friendly, property is very clean and comfortable. The kids loved the room, the view and the breakfast!
The location is a bit away from the main tourist attractions, but easy access to the metro and good casual dining spots nearby. Would highly recommend.

Excellent recently renovated hotel with great customer service . Breakfast is exceptional with lot of variety and quality of food is great.
Special thanks to Habibou for his great customer service . He is very kind and professional .
Overall great stay and my family enjoyed the stay

Great location - local train / metro stations, plenty of cafes nearby (3 mins walk). Lovely rooms, paid extra for city view - not worth it to be honest. Food in hotel over priced though and limited choice

My family and i styed there for 5 nights. The hotel have a modern touch recently renovated but unfortunately the corridors had a weird smell. The room was large with two double beds, clean ,comfortable the view from the window was not bad but nothing wow. Staff at the reception were very friendly and helpful, we check in in a few minutes and gave us a voucher for a free drink at the hotels lobby bar. Unfortunately we can't visit sky bar as my young daughter is 15 years old and was not allowed to go. One of the negative points for me is the location as it is located in the left bank of Paris so you need a taxi or metro everywhere you want to go.
Generally not bad hotel but nearly 400 euro per night without breakfast i think you can get much better and more centrally located.

The hotel is certainly modern and functional. We had a family room with two twin beds. It is pretty cramped with four pieces of luggage, but feasible. The view is nice, even if we had only a relatively small window and a limited angle of view. The gym is modern with three separate parts. The cushions are too thick, no thinner ones available after asking for it. The aircon is very noisy, and we heard loud working noises around 5 o’clock every night. There is always quite some staff in the entrance and lobby, but it feels more like security, i.e. not very welcoming. All in all, the hotel is functional, but it seems that the planners forgot that people also like to feel comfortable and at home.

Please note that the staff are IMPECCABLE at this hotel. They go above and beyond to help in every way possible.

The actual hotel itself has been fairly recently renovated, however, they did a poor job. Constant construction nearby, weird smells throughout the hotel, the A/C hardly worked anywhere in the building, there were stains on the sheets when we checked in, and worst of all the room was so ridiculously dusty we had to cut our stay short because of the irritation to our throats and noses. (We have lived in Paris before, so it was not the Parisian air). For nearly 400 euros you can get much much much better elsewhere. Had this hotel cost something in the range of 70-150 euros, it would make more sense.

This is a gem of a hotel in Paris. Few hotels in Paris accommodate a family of four in a room. Clean, modern and spacious room. The staff is vey helpful and professional in their attitude. The breakfast is excellent with plenty of variety . Three restaurants are at the Hotel, including Sky Bar. Train station is across the street and taxis are available right in front of the hotel. The concierge is helpful too. Plenty of restaurants in 10 minutes walking distance. Air conditioning was very efficient, despite Paris being in a middle of heatwave.

We stayed as a family with two teenagers and had interconnecting rooms. There was loads of space, the beds were very comfortable and the kids absolutely loved it. Great city view. We booked the hotel for the huge buffet breakfast which was good but we were very disappointed on our first morning to find the gluten free section of the buffet pretty empty. This was stress for us and our coeliac son. The following days there was no problem so maybe it was unfortunate timing. We had to order gluten free bread each day. There was no English Breakfast tea available, take your own bags if you love a brew! The hotel location was ok. The Edgar Quinet area by the metro was nice with some nice looking cafes and bars and a good Saturday morning market. We spent quite a lot of time on the metro on our trip getting to and from the hotel. This was ok but next time I’m in Paris I think I’d like to stay closer to the centre.

They asked me for a deposit of 800€ for eight nights plus the room already paid in advance

It never happen to me that hotel ask this huge amount of money just for deposite
And they never stated that on their website or booking site or voucher

I'll never stay again

We stayed here for two nights as part of a Viking tour. The room was spacious; however, the designer was obsessed with mirror. The concierge was friendly and helpful. Breakfast was a chaotic experience but the food was great. The location is perfect to access the main train station and Metro and good restaurants within walking distance.

Wonderful accommodations, unbelievably attentive staff that were always there to assist guests. Price for rooms were ‘just what we expected”. Good value. Umami restaurant staff were new and weren’t as trained as one would expect at this class of hotel.

Good Pullman in Paris. Good stay overall.
However when we arrived, check-in system and key making system was down. Pretty chaotic with a horde of American tourist waiting.

As an Accor platinum, there was no one in the special check-in lounge. I have to hunt for somebody.
Not much recognition as a platinum member, only welcome drink. No free room upgrade or any executive lounge access on this Pullman.

However, location is decent as it’s near train station if you are traveling to other French cities. Otherwise a good 10mins walk to nearby metro will get you into the heart of Paris.

Good room size for 3 of us. Comfy bed and overall good service per French standard, good breakfast, decent lively location, good local beer named Kiki and a good 4 days stay.

My family and I stayed in the hotel 3 nights which was wonderful.
great rooms very clean, and a great breakfast.
the hotel team service was great and very helpful.
great location.
Love to come back again.

Absolutely stunning hotel! All rooms were gorgeous (we had three) the views were amazing, great amenities and the staff were super helpful! Very modern and had everything we need, would stay here over and over. Thank you for everything !!!!!

We stayed as a family in a family room with two children aged 10 and 12. The room is large and has two double beds. It was comfortable for us.This hotel is not cheap but was pretty good value in relation to other comparable hotels in Paris

To travel to central Paris and all the sights is pretty easy on the metro, You can also take a taxi or Uber which we paid about €15 from central Paris. There are lots of restaurants locally if you don’t want to go into town for dinner with the family.

We did have a look at the Italian restaurant within the hotel but it’s not really suitable for children.

The checkin staff are excellent as is the concierge service who try their hardest to help you. They even provide us with umbrellas when it was raining.

Perhaps a weak point of the hotel is the breakfast and the service at breakfast. The selection of food is OK but it’s a bit chaotic.

Overall i would recommend they hotel for families or couples as a reasonably good value decent hotel in Paris .
There is a skybar ( we didn’t go as children not allowed)

The sky bar run separately from the hotel and you need to book on their separate website.

Pitiful service, obnoxious employees, lousy breakfast, horrible room design with no closet and drawer space. The desk does not respond to important issues like making sure we got our Covid response cards.

Nice hotel but no internet to speak of and no good dinner restaurant . It was modern but tub/ shower very high for older people! Good breakfast but only a hamburger place for dinner. We stayed three night. It also was in the west of Paris so not very centrally located.

The hotel staff were helpful and the breakfast was extraordinary. Our room looked great and the bed was comfortable. However, the hair dryer was not reportedly senior friendly, requiring constant pressure to operate, and the shower had a slippery floor, no grab bars and inscrutable controls. While the immediate blocks are corporate charmless, if you walk several blocks you’ll find the Boulevard Montparnasse and good cafes. And of course the Montparnasse tower, the catacombs, the cemetery and a convenient transit connection. I think it’s good if you want a corporate type hotel near transit, with pleasant dining options within walking distance.

We recently stayed at the Pullman Paris Montparnasse Hotel for 6 nights. The hotel is lovely, clean, and very comfortable. They excelled in customer service at every level. From the bellman, to the concierge, the front desk to the restaurant servers, the housekeepers to the hotel manager, we felt like treasured guests. The staff at the hotel constantly went out of their way to make sure we were happy and taken care of. I would not hesitate to recommend this hotel. There are multiple very good restaurants within a few minutes walk, as well as public transportation moments from the hotel. Don't miss the view from the sky bar.

Stayed at his newly refurbished hotel for a business trip. The rooms were clean and modern with a great rainfall shower. Plenty of usb points and even a U.K. electric socket, perfect for my laptop.

Staff were super helpful and couldn't do enough to make your stay a very pleasant one. Breakfast was vast and everything you need. If you do have time in the evening, make sure you visit the sky bar with unparalleled views of the Eiffel Tower.

We are staying at the beautiful Pullman Paris Montparnasse. Lovely clean rooms with excellent service in the rooms. The staff is friendly and helpful everywhere. It feels like a safe and convenient place in town. Felt like home. We will definitely stay again.😁

Maxime, local expert, was amazing, personable and knowledgeable and very friendly. We are impressed and will stay at Pullman again thanks to our experience in Paris. Customer Service is very important when we travel and when a hotel team goes above and beyond it enhances the entire trip.

Our stay was great. We will definitely visit again. We were greeted very well, and got a room immediately, even though we came before check-in. The staff was very helpful, and gave great advise. Lastly at the end of our trip we where wished a “Bon voyage“ by Domenic, which tied the whole experience nicely together.
It was superb from the beginning to the end.

Our Paris tour company booked us at this hotel, our stay was very enjoyable. The location of this hotel is great, many walkable restaurants and great access to the Montparnasse train/metro/bus station. Our room was very comfy and had nice city views. The room and the rest of the hotel was very clean and modern inside. An added bonus was the breakfast buffet, a fabulous assortment of breakfast foods (hot and cold). Highly recommend!!

Perfect hotel, friendly staff, very nice decorated hotel and in the heart of the city. Fantastic view from the room above Paris. The breakfast and the restaurant were splendid and very good. We come again!

Recently refreshed with 3 years of renovation, this hotel is still a good place to host for my parisian business travels. Bedrooms have been revisited with taste
Very pleasant stay for me in this hotel

Staff at reception are incredibly Friendly. We got a room with a view but there isn’t anything fantastic about the view. Everything is very new since the hotel opened last year. We also couldn’t go up to the sky bar since we were told it was too busy. I wished the bathrooms would have doors not just a curtain, and it would help if the shower area had a shower door too to prevent water splashing out.

My husband and I stayed for a week and cannot say enough good things about the staff. Gary, Maria Rosette, and Hua are absolutely amazing and I consider them friends now. Gary is a phenomenal bartender! Maria Rosette is so friendly! Hua is so smart and kind! All of the staff are so nice and accommodating. The views are spectacular and the rooms are nice and clean. Highly recommend! :)

I was blown away by the service in this hotel. The staff are amazingly well trained and knew my name within hours after check in. Jean, one of the concierges greeted us each night and arranged tickets for a special art exhibit in town. Had I known how helpful he and his colleagues would be I would have had them book all of our tours. He and his colleague left a special “One Day in Paris” series of cards with directions to a day’s activities for a first time visitor like my travel companion, complete with transit directions and dinner suggestions.
There is really good security in the hotel and each and every person wants to help. The SkyBar has amazing views and small bites. It is located right by the Metro and Train station to take you throughout the city and beyond. Finally, this would be a great spot for families as well as wheelchair bound visitors as the hotel is very well set up for accessibility.

Great hotel close to the Montparnasse train . The hotel recently opened and looks quite modern with beautiful interior spaces. The American restaurant is really good. Can't wait to check out the Skybar once it is open. Everyone was super friendly. A big thank you to the entire hotel team and especially to Adrien who was just amazing. I felt like a real star during the visit.

Stayed between Christmas and New Year after we had to reorganize our trip originally planned to New York.

The hotel is fantastic, brand new, very comfortable beds and great showers.

Breakfast is an absolute killer and we were spoiled with choice.

Just checked in and already prepared to give a five star rating. Margaux and Dominic were excellent and went out of their way to assist. The hotel is newly opened and as expected very modern although the colours are not to my taste. Looking forward to visiting the Sky Bar and the remainder of the stay here. Will update this review later.

First off, The Pullman Montparnasse is in a great location, basically across the street from Gare Montparnasse for the Metro and RER trains. If you want easy access to transit, this place is for you-this is very important to me! Everything was clean but the room lacked any kind of Parisian charm. It seems to be geared more to the business traveler than tourists looking for French touches but really no big deal as we were gone most of the time. Beds were REALLY comfy, good sheets, etc. Big bathroom and yes, there's a bidet ;-) Our 14th floor room had the most incredible view and you could see the Eiffel tower which as a tourist was an added bonus. Breakfast was so much better than expected (it was included so I figured a stale croissant & coffee but no!!) with all kinds of breads, eggs, sausages, fresh juice, coffee and the best yogurt I've ever tasted (in little glass jars, SO good!) Also, everything you need is done through the TV...let me explain. If you ask for a wakeup call, the TV goes on at said time. If you get a fax (which we did), a message appears on the TV. Instead of outdated room service menus and binders in your room, you access everything via the TV. You can check your bill daily to see your ongoing charges. Which leads me to my only complaint...the refrigerator in the room has snacks and drinks. We didn't eat or drink anything but were charged everyday when we moved things around to make room for our Coke's (it was promptly corrected). Guess there's a sensor so I would advise just laying your items on top. Bottom line, would I stay here again, yes!!!
